'''小行星3122'''（{{lang-en|3122 Florence}}，中文多直譯為'''佛羅倫斯'''）是一颗围绕[[太阳|太阳]][[公转|公转]]的[[小行星|小行星]]。1981年3月2日，[[舒爾特·巴斯|舒爾特·巴斯]]在赛丁泉山发现了此天体<ref name="a" /><ref>{{cite news|title=小行星列表|url=http://cfa-www.harvard.edu/iau/lists/NumberedMPs.txt|accessdate=2013-07-08|newspaper=哈佛大学|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080517010638/http://cfa-www.harvard.edu/iau/lists/NumberedMPs.txt|archivedate=2008-05-17}}</ref>。

这颗小行星的[[绝对星等|绝对星等]]为{{val|13.87|0.1}}<ref name="a" />。

==卫星==
[[Image:3122_Florence_with_moons.jpg|thumb]]
2017年发现小行星3122有两颗[[卫星|卫星]]。直径约在100-300米，内环卫星环绕一周大约8小时，外环卫星大约22-27小时。<ref>{{cite news|title=Radar reveals two moons orbiting asteroid Florence – Astronomy Now|url=https://astronomynow.com/2017/09/05/radar-reveals-two-moons-orbiting-asteroid-florence/|accessdate=2017-09-13|work=Astronomy Now|publisher=2017-09-05 |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906053005/https://astronomynow.com/2017/09/05/radar-reveals-two-moons-orbiting-asteroid-florence/|archivedate=2017-09-06}}</ref>

==2017年飞掠地球==
2017年9月1日，小行星3122从距离地球{{convert|0.047237|AU|km mi|abbr=on|lk=on}}处飞掠而过，该距离约为地月距离的18倍。由地球观之，该小行星的[[视星等|视星等]]达到8.5。小行星3122由南向北越过[[南鱼座|南鱼座]]、[[摩羯座|摩羯座]]、[[宝瓶座|宝瓶座]]时，人们可以通过小型天文望远镜观测之，时间长达数个夜晚。2017年的飞掠地球是其1890年以来至2050年间最近的一次。<ref>{{cite news|title=Nasa says big asteroid to pass safely by Earth on 1 September|url=http://www.livemint.com/Science/0Far3fmQLS4Bq6kUXKrMjM/Nasa-says-big-asteroid-to-pass-safely-by-Earth-on-1-Septembe.html|agency=Livemint|date=2017-08-18|author=PTI|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170820061321/http://www.livemint.com/Science/0Far3fmQLS4Bq6kUXKrMjM/Nasa-says-big-asteroid-to-pass-safely-by-Earth-on-1-Septembe.html|archivedate=2017-08-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skyandtelescope.com/observing/see-asteroid-florence-fly-by-earth-this-week/|title=Asteroid Florence Pays Earth a Visit - Sky & Telescope|date=30 August 2017|publisher=|accessdate=1 September 2017|archive-date=2018-09-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180903022158/https://www.skyandtelescope.com/observing/see-asteroid-florence-fly-by-earth-this-week/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://astrobob.areavoices.com/2017/08/30/see-florence-one-of-largest-near-earth-asteroids-zip-by-earth/|title=See Florence, One Of The Largest Near-Earth Asteroids, Zip By Earth|date=2017-08-30|publisher=|accessdate=2017-09-01|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170831190003/http://astrobob.areavoices.com/2017/08/30/see-florence-one-of-largest-near-earth-asteroids-zip-by-earth/|archivedate=2017-08-31}}</ref>上次该小行星飞掠地球发生于1930年8月29日，最近距地球距离为0.05239 AU，预计下次飞掠地球将发生于2057年9月2日，最近距地球距离为0.049952 AU。<ref>{{cite web |url=https://echo.jpl.nasa.gov/asteroids/Florence/Florence_planning.html |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2017-08-24 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161118020825/http://echo.jpl.nasa.gov/asteroids/Florence/Florence_planning.html |archivedate=2016-11-18 }}</ref>

天文学家通过在[[阿雷西博天文台|阿雷西博天文台]]的观测，发现该小行星有两颗卫星。<ref name=":0">[https://cneos.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news199.html Radar Reveals Two Moons Orbiting Asteroid Florence] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170903060914/https://cneos.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news199.html |date=2017-09-03 }}, Sep 1, 2017</ref><ref name="moons">{{cite web| url=https://twitter.com/NAICobservatory/status/903831035187793920| title=Arecibo announcement of the two moons (Twitter)| date=2017-09-02 | publisher=Arecibo Observatory| deadurl=no| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170902111346/https://twitter.com/naicobservatory/status/903831035187793920| archivedate=2017-09-02}}</ref>

